We performed an approximate simulation of the Starship atmospheric entry for each entry trajectory. The hyperbolic trajectory, generated from the Lambert’s problem solution, was numerically propagated through Earth and Mars’ upper atmosphere. Earth’s atmosphere was modeled by COESA7640 while Mars’ used an exponential model empirically fit to NASA measurements41. We assumed a constant lift to drag ratio of 0.542, and an inverted \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
