				\begin{document}$$1.84\pm 0.33$$\end{document} mSv per day47 which does not significantly change with distance to the Sun during a Mars mission. Thus the radiation dosage for a 90-day transit is halved from a 180-day transit. Assuming significant shielding on the surface of Mars (which can be provided by local materials such as ice and Mars dirt), the radiation during transit will be the majority of the total mission radiation. This is \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
